Rating: 0
The recipe calls for removing the rhubarb from the wine before it falls apart, which I never manage to do, but the results are amazing anyway. I just fish out whatever rhubarb is still intact and reduce the wine/sugar less than it calls for. This recipe also makes amazing sorbet, pureed and frozen in an ice cream freezer. (I use 3 cups in my 1.5-quart machine.)

